9    /**
10    * A DataNode which can have child nodes, meaning it is
11    * an internal node in a data tree storing named values.
12    * Any DataValueNode (the leaf node with value) must be a
13    * child of a DataGroupNode, and the group nodes can also
14    * make a tree structure of any depth. Implementing the
15    * DataNode interface, child nodes can be retrieved.
16    * DataGroupNode adds methods for adding and removing child
17    * nodes, as well as additional retrieval methods. External
18    * code will typically interact with the data structure
19    * through the DataHandle interface, in which case changes
20    * to the structure should be through that interface, not
21    * directly on node objects.
22    *
23    * @author Lars Thomas Boye, Tellu AS
24    */

265    /**
266    * Adds a child node to the group, checking relevant meta-data.
267    * The node added can NOT have meta data. It will be assigned
268    * any meta found in the collection with matching name. The node
269    * added, as well as any children, will have the modified flag
270    * set. Applying meta is recursive, so that if the group has a
271    * tree of meta and the added node has a tree of nodes with
272    * matching names, meta will be applied to the added tree.
273    * <p>
274    * The method throws a DataRestrictionException if the operation

276    * have been partially applied to the new node before failing,
